dcterms:description: A comprehensive collection of chess games, renowned for featuring high-quality matches played by grandmasters and skilled players. The dataset is filtered to include only games played by individuals rated at least 2200 Elo and excludes games shorter than five moves.
dcterms:title: Kingbase Lite 2019

dcterms:description: A dataset that categorizes chess positions into distinct phases: opening, middlegame, and endgame, based on specific criteria such as board mixedness and piece count.
dcterms:title: Lichess Game Phase Definitions

dcterms:description: A dataset containing chess positions that do not belong to any specific game phase, used for training and evaluation purposes.
dcterms:title: No-Phases Dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset containing chess positions specifically from the opening phase of the game, used for training and evaluation purposes.
dcterms:title: Opening Dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset containing chess positions specifically from the middlegame phase of the game, used for training and evaluation purposes.
dcterms:title: Midgame Dataset

dcterms:description: A dataset containing chess positions specifically from the endgame phase of the game, used for training and evaluation purposes.
dcterms:title: Endgame Dataset
